summary:
The Security Council:
Recalling previous resolutions on Liberia and West Africa, particularly resolutions 1521 (2003) and 1532 (2004),
 Takes note of reports on Liberia and decides to re-establish the Panel of Experts for a further period until 21 December 2004 to:
  (a) assess implementation and violations of measures imposed on Liberia, including arms trade and diamond and timber exports;
  (b) evaluate progress towards goals set out in resolution 1521 (2003);
  (c) monitor implementation of measures imposed by resolution 1532 (2004);
  (d) assess socio-economic and humanitarian impact;
 Requests the Panel to provide a mid-term report by 30 September 2004 and a final report by 10 December 2004;
 Requests the Secretary-General to appoint experts by 30 June 2004 and make necessary financial arrangements;
 Encourages the National Transitional Government of Liberia (NTGL) to establish an effective Certificate of Origin regime for Liberian rough diamonds and ensure government control over timber producing areas;
 Urges NTGL to use government revenues from timber for legitimate purposes;
 Reiterates calls for assistance to NTGL and appeals for timely and adequate assistance for Liberia's reconstruction and economic recovery;
 Urges cooperation with the Committee and Panel of Experts;
 Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
